translation.Name: Buak_Note_25
translation.Interactability_Text_Line_2: I have cleaned a LOT of blood in my time here, MORE than I’m comfortable with, but I noticed something that none of the lab coats have. The blood ALWAYS remains fresh. It dries up like normal, but over time blood should turn brown, but this doesn’t. It’s always the same colour. Is this worth reporting? Not sure, I just get paid to clean.
